==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isocyanic
<hw>I`so*cy*an"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets>
+ <ets>cyanic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Designating an acid
isomeric with cyanic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Isocyanic acid</b></col>, <cd>an acid metameric with
cyanic acid, and resembling it in its salts. It is obtained as a
colorless, mobile, unstable liquid by the heating cyanuric acid. Called
technically <altname>carbimide</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isocyanuric</ent>⟦br⟧
